<subSubSection id="D69D654E834F1F69FA7DF997FDBBFE76" lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="20" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="9E3836C5834F1F69FA7DF997FDBBFE76" blockId="18.[264,1324,1567,1873]" lastBlockId="19.[264,1322,284,390]" lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="20" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis id="ACF3EAD7834F1F68FA7DF997FEFBF9C8" box="[264,374,1567,1592]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Remarks.</emphasis>
There is a problem with the nomenclature of this well­known and widely distributed species as there appears to be an older name, 
<taxonomicName id="59874D46834F1F68F811F9CFFB7DF991" authority="Forskal, 1775" authorityName="Forskal" authorityYear="1775" box="[868,1264,1607,1633]" class="Malacostraca" family="Cancridae" genus="Cancer" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tridentatus">
<emphasis id="ACF3EAD7834F1F68F811F9CFFBCFF990" box="[868,1090,1607,1632]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Cancer tridentatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="FA164B34834F1F68FF3FF9CFFB7DF991" author="Forskal" box="[1098,1264,1607,1633]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" refString="Forskal, P. (1775) Descriptiones Animalium, Avium, Amphibiorum, Piscium, Insectorum, Vermium. Hafniae, 19 + xxxii + 164 pp." type="book" year="1775">
Forskål, 
<number id="284F24E2834F1F68FFC7F9CFFB7DF991" box="[1202,1264,1607,1633]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="1775.0">1775</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The original description of 
<taxonomicName id="59874D46834F1F68F961F9E7FC14F979" authority="Forskal, 1775" authorityName="Forskal" authorityYear="1775" box="[532,921,1647,1673]" class="Malacostraca" family="Cancridae" genus="Cancer" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tridentatus">
<emphasis id="ACF3EAD7834F1F68F961F9E7FD7CF978" box="[532,753,1647,1672]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Cancer tridentatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="FA164B34834F1F68F98DF9E7FC14F979" author="Forskal" box="[760,921,1647,1673]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" refString="Forskal, P. (1775) Descriptiones Animalium, Avium, Amphibiorum, Piscium, Insectorum, Vermium. Hafniae, 19 + xxxii + 164 pp." type="book" year="1775">
Forskål, 
<number id="284F24E2834F1F68F82BF9E7FC14F979" box="[862,921,1647,1673]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="1775.0">1775</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(from Suez, Red Sea), is too brief to be certain of its identity, but as it is, it fits the genus 
<taxonomicName id="59874D46834F1F68F8EFF91FFB89F940" box="[922,1028,1687,1712]" class="Malacostraca" family="Domeciidae" genus="Domecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="ACF3EAD7834F1F68F8EFF91FFB89F940" box="[922,1028,1687,1712]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Domecia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as presently understood. The description best fits 
<taxonomicName id="59874D46834F1F68F95EF937FBCFF929" authority="Eydoux and Souleyet, 1842" authorityName="Eydoux and Souleyet" authorityYear="1842" box="[555,1090,1727,1753]" class="Malacostraca" family="Domeciidae" genus="Domecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hispida">
<emphasis id="ACF3EAD7834F1F68F95EF937FD7FF928" box="[555,754,1727,1752]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Domecia hispida</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="FA164B34834F1F68F98FF937FBCFF929" author="Eydoux" box="[762,1090,1727,1753]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" refString="Eydoux, F. &amp; Souleyet, F. A. (1842) Crustaces. In: Voyage autour du monde execute pendant les annees 1836 et 1837 sur la corvette la Bonite, commandee par M. Vaillant. Zoologie, 1 (2), 107 - 328; Atlas, pls. 1 - 150." type="journal article" year="1842">
Eydoux and Souleyet, 
<number id="284F24E2834F1F68FF71F937FBCFF929" box="[1028,1090,1727,1753]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="1842.0">1842</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which is present in the Red Sea. As Forskål's material is no longer extant, we can never be certain. However, to have the senior name replacing the widely used name of 
<taxonomicName id="59874D46834F1F68F8C9F887FB09F8D8" box="[956,1156,1807,1832]" class="Malacostraca" family="Domeciidae" genus="Domecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hispida">
<emphasis id="ACF3EAD7834F1F68F8C9F887FB09F8D8" box="[956,1156,1807,1832]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Domecia hispida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
serves no real purpose in our opinion, and we invoke Article 23.9. 
<number id="284F24E2834F1F68F817F8BFFCFCF8A1" box="[866,881,1847,1873]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="2.0">2</number>
of the current zoological code in suppressing the senior name. Certainly, the name 
<taxonomicName id="59874D46834E1F69F853FE94FB23FEC6" authority="Forskal, 1775" authorityName="Forskal" authorityYear="1775" box="[806,1198,284,310]" class="Malacostraca" family="Cancridae" genus="Cancer" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tridentatus">
<emphasis id="ACF3EAD7834E1F69F853FE94FB8EFEC5" box="[806,1027,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Cancer tridentatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="FA164B34834E1F69FF7EFE94FB23FEC6" author="Forskal" box="[1035,1198,284,310]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" refString="Forskal, P. (1775) Descriptiones Animalium, Avium, Amphibiorum, Piscium, Insectorum, Vermium. Hafniae, 19 + xxxii + 164 pp." type="book" year="1775">
Forskål, 
<number id="284F24E2834E1F69FF04FE94FB23FEC6" box="[1137,1198,284,310]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="1775.0">1775</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, has never been used since its description while the name 
<taxonomicName id="59874D46834E1F69F84BFECCFB8AFEAD" box="[830,1031,324,349]" class="Malacostraca" family="Domeciidae" genus="Domecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hispida">
<emphasis id="ACF3EAD7834E1F69F84BFECCFB8AFEAD" box="[830,1031,324,349]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Domecia hispida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been regularly used over the last few decades.
</paragraph>
